PostgreSQL is an open-source SQL database used to store, manage, and retrieve data for applications.

In simple words:
PostgreSQL is a powerful database that stores data in tables (rows and columns) and helps applications read and write data safely and efficiently.

Easy example

If you build a web app with users, orders, or messages, PostgreSQL stores all that information and makes sure it stays accurate, secure, and fast.

Why developers use PostgreSQL

It is reliable and secure

Handles large amounts of data

Supports complex queries

Works very well with Python, Django, and FastAPI

One-line definition (interview-ready):

PostgreSQL is a reliable relational database that stores structured data and supports complex queries using SQL.
